EASTERN CAPE - One of the five police officers gunned down at eNgcobo in the Eastern Cape last week, is being laid to rest on Friday. Warrant Officer Zuko Mbini's funeral is at his home in Vidgesville, outside Mthatha. WATCH: We alerted everyone, but no-one acted Last week, seven suspects were gun down in a shootout with police. They were found in their hide-out at Mancoba Seven Angel Ministries. So far six suspects have been arrested in connection with the incident. eNCA